<item>
            <title>[CASSANDRA-3239] can&apos;t use RackInferringSnitch and CQL JDBC&apos;s &quot;CREATE KEYSPACE&quot; with NetworkTopologyStrategy</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-3239</link>
                <project id="12310865" key="CASSANDRA">Apache Cassandra</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;If using the CQL JDBC driver, there&apos;s a problem with using RackInferringSnitch&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;1. With RackInferringSnitch, the datacenter names are numeric&lt;br/&gt;
2. With CQL and NetworkTopologyStrategy, the data center replicas are specified as strategy_options:&amp;lt;dc-name&amp;gt;=&amp;lt;#-of-replicas&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
3. Using a number for &amp;lt;dc-name&amp;gt; fails&lt;br/&gt;
4. Using a quoted number for &amp;lt;dc-name&amp;gt; fails&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
