                            <comment id="13112304" author="jbellis" created="Thu, 22 Sep 2011 03:54:10 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Note: if the fix is complicated let&apos;s target it for 1.0.0&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13112761" author="jbellis" created="Thu, 22 Sep 2011 17:57:52 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;What is &quot;compident?&quot; I&apos;m pretty sure we don&apos;t want to allow int-as-ident in most places.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13112814" author="xedin" created="Thu, 22 Sep 2011 18:41:39 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;If I understand everything correctly it means &quot;composite identifier&quot; and it is only used by &quot;CREATE SCHEMA&quot; statement.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13115687" author="xedin" created="Tue, 27 Sep 2011 16:28:08 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;rebased with the latest cassandra-0.8 branch and COMPIDENT changed to support integers only at the second part.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
